\par }}{\*\pnseclvl1\pnucrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl2\pnucltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl3\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl4\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl5\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl6\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl7\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl8\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl9\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}\pard\plain \li-90\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b\f1\fs22 1. Read the passage given below and identify one quality that it describes to become an authorized teacher of Bhagavad gita.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \li360\ri180\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 \sect }\sectd \marglsxn1440\margrsxn1440\psz1\sbknone\linex0\cols2\colsx360\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li270\ri-90\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f1\fs22 In the material world also, suppose if we want to learn the art of music, then we have to find out somebody who is a musician.  Without having the association of a musician, nobody can learn the art of music, or any art.  Suppose if one wants to become an engineer, then one has to go to an engineering college or technical college and learn all the relevant subjects there.  Nobody can become a medical practitioner just by purchasing books from the market and reading at home.  That is not possible.  You have to admit yourself in a medical college and undergo training and practical examination. Simply by purchasing book, it is not possible. Therefore it is stated in Bhagavad-gita that if we at all want to learn transcendental knowledge, we must approach one who has actually seen the Absolute Truth.\sect }\sectd \marglsxn1440\margrsxn1440\psz1\sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li360\ri180\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \li360\ri180\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par In order to understand transcendental science, one must approach a bona fide spiritual master, hear from him submissively, and render service to him. Lord Krishna explains this in the Bhagavad-gita Fourth Chapter Text 34:
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \qc\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i\f1\fs22 tad viddhi pranipatena pariprasnena sevaya
\par }\pard \qc\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i\f1\fs22 updeksyanti te jnanam jnaninas tattva darsinah
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 \ldblquote Just try to learn the truth by approaching a spiritual master. Inquire from him submissively and render service unto him. The self realized souls can impart knowledge unto you because they have seen the truth.\rdblquote 
\par 
