\par }{\b\f1\fs22 
\par 2. Please read the following paragraph carefully and mention the quality required to be an authorized teacher of Bhagavad Gita:}{\f1\fs22 
\par }{\f1\fs18 
\par }\pard \qc\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 sa evayam maya te 'dya yogah proktah puratanah
\par }\pard \qc\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 bhakto 'si me sakha ceti rahasyam hy etad uttamam
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f1\fs22 
\par \ldblquote That very ancient science of the relationship with the Supreme is today told by Me to you because you are My devotee as well as My friend and can therefore understand the transcendental mystery of this science.\rdblquote 
\par 
\par      }{\f1\fs22 There are two classes of men, namely the devotee and the demon. The Lord selected Arjuna as the recipient of this great science because of his being a devotee of the Lord, but for the demon it is not possible to understand this great mysterious science. Arjuna accepts Sri Krishna as the Supreme Personality of Godhead, hence he was perfectly qualified to receive this transcendental knowledge. Bhagavad-gita is a treatise which can be understood and told by the devotee of the Lord.
\par }{\f1\fs18 
\par 
\par 
