\par }{\b\f1\fs22 
\par 5. Read the passage given below and identify one quality that it describes to become an authorized teacher of Bhagavad gita.
\par }{\f1\fs22 
\par Without becoming free from sins can one not understand the Absolute truth ?
\par Certainly you can\rquote t. As you become purified, then you become qualified to receive the spiritual knowledge. Therefore that is stated in the Bhagavad-gita Chapter seven Text 28:
\par 
\par }\pard \qc\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i\f1\fs22 yesam tv anta-gatam papam jananam punya-karmanam
\par }\pard \qc\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i\f1\fs22 te dvandva-moha-nirmukta bhajante mam drdha-vratah
\par }{\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f1\fs22 \ldblquote Persons who have acted piously in previous lives and in this life and whose sinful actions are completely eradicated are freed from the dualities of delusion, and they engage themselves in My service with determination.\rdblquote 
\par }{\f1\fs22 
\par "One who has finished his sinful life, he can know this science of God." So long one is sinful, the spiritual knowledge will not be properly manifested.
\par One who is completely free from all contamination of material modes, }{\i\f1\fs22 anta-gatam papam}{\f1\fs22 : sinful activities. He can, }{\i\f1\fs22 te dvandva-moha-nirmukta bhajante mam}{\f1\fs22 , he can understand principle of devotional service. Otherwise, if one is not free from the contamination of sinful life then one lacks the qualification to understand this Absolute science..}{\f1\fs18 
\par 
