\par }{\b\f1\fs22 
\par 6. Following is an excerpt from a conversation between  Srila Prabhupada and John Lennon ( the famous Beatles Singer ) in London at the farm house of George Harrison ( another Beatles star ). Please read carefully and mention the quality required to be an authorized teacher of Bhagavad Gita:}{\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 John Lennon:}{\f1\fs22  What do you mean by receiving through "channel" ? Is it through hereditary or what?
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 \sect }\sectd \marglsxn1440\margrsxn1440\psz1\sbknone\linex0\cols2\colsx360\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b\f1\fs22 Prabhupada:}{\f1\fs22  Just like channel... you will understand very easily by this example. You send some money order to your friend. So from which channel he will receive? He will receive through the post office, not through any other channel. So if the postman delivers it, you are confident, "Yes, the money has come." So why do you give the importance to the postman ? Because he is representative of the post office. Similarly, Krishna is the original authority. So Krishna's representative is the authority. 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 And who is Krishna's representative? Who is a devotee of Krishna! So therefore the devotee of Krishna is authority, at least of Bhagavad-gita. So you have to receive through the devotee of Krishna about Bhagavad-gita. One who does not know anything about Krishna, how he can preach Bhagavad-gita? This is common sense. I may be imperfect, but because I understand Bhagavad-gita as it was understood by Arjuna, I am perfect. Because the knowledge I am distributing, that is not imperfect. So a postman may be poor man, but the one thousand rupees, he is delivering, that is a fact. That is not bogus thing. Because he has not manufactured something. He has received that money order from the post office. He's asked to deliver it to such and such person. His honesty is to deliver the money order as it is to the bona fide person. He is honestly carrying that money and delivering you.
\par Similarly, a guru, a guru is perfect when he delivers the words of the superior authority as it is. Then he's perfect. He may be imperfect in ordinary estimation. But that is his perfection, that he is not misleading people by becoming a so-called scholar and interpreting in a different way and misleading the whole population. He is presenting the message as it is.
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 \sect }\sectd \marglsxn1440\margrsxn1440\psz1\sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b\f1\fs18 
